      <div class="article-teaser">
        We are working on long-term plans to transform the northern and southern roundabouts at Lambeth Bridge. If we decide to go ahead with our proposals, we could start construction late in 2021.
        
      </div>
    
    
      <p>We consulted on the plans between June and August 2017. We plan to publish the consultation report in the first half of 2020 on our <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/lambeth-bridge">Lambeth Bridge consultation page</a>.</p>

<h2>Improvements</h2>

<p>During spring 2017 we made changes to improve safety for vulnerable road users at the northern roundabout.</p>

<p>The changes were intended to improve safety quickly, while we investigated long-term plans to re-design the junction. This project is now complete.</p>

<p>We have:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Widened footways and extended traffic islands to reduce traffic speeds and provide more space for pedestrians</li>
	<li>Raised zebra crossings on all four sides of the junction to slow traffic on the approach to the roundabout</li>
	<li>Installed clearer lane markings at the roundabout</li>
</ul>
      
           
      
